        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 2 at 7:53PM EDT until August 2 at 9:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following counties, Beaufort, Charleston, Colleton and Jasper.

* WHEN...Until 900 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 749 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated numerous showers and
thunderstorms with torrential rainfall extending from Yonges
Island and Edisto Island west to near Gillisonville and
Okatie. As much as 1 to 3 inches of rain have fallen in these
areas since early this evening with the highest amounts
occurring across Beaufort County. An additional 1 to 2 inches
can be expected through 9 PM. There is a risk for minor
flooding of low-lying and poor drainage areas.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Beaufort, Port Royal, Ridgeland, Edisto Beach, Johns Island,
Clarendon, Jasper, Hollywood, Ravenel and Seabrook Island.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
